The paper deals with the development of subjective and objective measures to identify and quantify various types of Perceivable Encoding Artifacts (PEAs) in compressed videos. This involves the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and the definition of PEA pattern and PEA intensity measures. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
